# <PROJECT> — Invariant Registry

> **1 invariant = 1 entry = 1 mutation-probed scan.** This registry is the single home of "what must always
> be true," and every entry is backed by a named, executable scan. Earned: one project accumulated 15
> per-slice conformance files (5,251 lines, 323 assertions) asserting the same invariants in three places
> with hand-copied regexes — discovering what was pinned required slice archaeology. Consolidate here instead.

## Rules
- **An invariant without a scan is a wish** (Governance §15 mechanism-over-prose). New invariant ⇒ new scan in the same PR.
- **Every scan is mutation-probed at least once**: plant the violation → exactly the named scan goes red → restore byte-identical (record the probe date below). A guard that never tripped under sabotage is unverified.
- Slices reference entries by ID (the slice template's "Invariants touched" field); amending an entry requires the owning signature (gates-change-by-signature).
- Binding §0-class invariants (the project's never-regress list) live in the router's hand half AND here — the router states them; this registry binds them to scans.

## Registry
